OL,3,CEngland's Red Roses celebrate fifth
OL,4,CGrand Slam after defeating France
OL,6,FThey knew France - their closest
OL,7,FEuropean rivals ` had meant business
OL,8,Ffrom the moment their defence was
OL,9,Fbreached by a stunning try from deep
OL,10,Fthat was given momentum by wing Lea
OL,11,FMurie and ended with Bourdon Sansus
OL,12,Farriving at full tilt to finish.
OL,14,FThe hosts continued to threaten with
OL,15,FMurie and Anais Grando on the opposite
OL,16,Fwing causing problems, but they were
OL,17,Fmaking too many errors.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
