OL,3,CEngland's Red Roses celebrate fifth
OL,4,CGrand Slam after defeating France
OL,6,FFrance were still asking questions of
OL,7,Fthe visiting defence but mistakes
OL,8,Fcontinued to haunt them, including in
OL,9,Fdefence when Murie failed to tackle
OL,10,FBreach when the England wing picked up
OL,11,Fa loose pass and raced over.
OL,13,FKildunne switched on the afterburners
OL,14,Ffor her second after capitalising on
OL,15,Fan overlap and, with Zoe Harrison
OL,16,Flanding all four conversions, the Red
OL,17,FRoses were 26-7 ahead at half-time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
