OL,3,CEngland's Red Roses celebrate fifth
OL,4,CGrand Slam after defeating France
OL,6,FFrance called on their history of
OL,7,Fcomebacks against England to respond
OL,8,Fwith two quick tries, both run in by
OL,9,Ftheir half-back general Bourdon Sansus.
OL,11,FTwo classy scores by Bourdon Sansus
OL,12,Fhad blown the game wide open but
OL,13,FFrance's reply ran out of steam and it
OL,14,Fwas Breach who went over next with
OL,15,FKildunne's straight line giving her a
OL,16,Ffinisher's chance.
OL,18,FBreach left three tacklers in her wake
OL,19,Fto place England on the brink of glory
OL,20,Fand the final stages swung
OL,21,Fconclusively against the hosts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
